347":"1271–1347","1291–1365":"1291–1365","1295–Female":"1295–Deceased","1250–1310":"1250–1310","about 1291":"about 1291","1295":"1295","1250":"1250","1271":"1271","1291":"1291","1347":"1347","Bef 24 November 1310":"before 24 November 1310","24 May 1310":"24 May 1310","Abt 1265":"about 1265","1365":"1365","1310":"1310","1265":"1265","about 1295":"about 1295","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Scarborough, North Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Scarborough, North Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Scarborough, Yorkshire, England":"Scarborough, Yorkshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Ughtred","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Outred  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Outred","meanings":["English: (i) relationship name from the Middle English personal name  <i>Utred</i>,  <i>Oughtred</i> (Old English  <i>Ūhtrǣd</i>, a compound of  <i>ūht</i> of unknown meaning +  <i>rǣd</i> ‘advice’). (ii) the name may sometimes have been confused with, or be a phonetic variant of   Outridge  . Compare George Outrid, 1682, with George Outridge, 1685 in   IGI   (Cuckfield, Sussex)."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Ughtred was born about 1265 as the son of Robert Oughtred Sir. He married Isabel Steeton about 1291, in Yorkshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died before 24 November 1310."},"et":{"Abt 1265–Bef 24 November 1310":"umbes 1265–enne 24. novembrit 1310","1265–1310":"1265–1310","1271–1347":"1271–1347","1291–1365":"1291–1365","1295–Female":"1295–Surnud","1250–1310":"1250–1310","about 1291":"umbes 1291","1295":"1295","1250":"1250","1271":"1271","1291":"1291","1347":"1347","Bef 24 November 1310":"enne 24. novembrit 1310","24 May 1310":"24. mai 1310","Abt 1265":"umbes 1265","1365":"1365","1310":"1310","1265":"1265","about 1295":"umbes 1295","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Scarborough, North Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Scarborough, North Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Scarborough, Yorkshire, England":"Scarborough, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1265–Bef 24 November 1310":"noin 1265–ennen vuotta 24. marraskuuta 1310","1265–1310":"1265–1310","1271–1347":"1271–1347","1291–1365":"1291–1365","1295–Female":"1295–Kuollut","1250–1310":"1250–1310","about 1291":"noin 1291","1295":"1295","1250":"1250","1271":"1271","1291":"1291","1347":"1347","Bef 24 November 1310":"ennen vuotta 24. marraskuuta 1310","24 May 1310":"24. toukokuuta 1310","Abt 1265":"noin 1265","1365":"1365","1310":"1310","1265":"1265","about 1295":"noin 1295","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Scarborough, North Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Scarborough, North Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Scarborough, Yorkshire, England":"Scarborough, Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"Abt 1265–Bef 24 November 1310":"environ 1265–avant 24 novembre 1310","1265–1310":"1265–1310","1271–1347":"1271–1347","1291–1365":"12